revisions.rev:
A comparison of notable '''[[screencasting]] [[software]]''' programs, that are used to record activities on the [[computer]] screen, mouse movement, and often includes live audio for later playback. Screencasting is an asynchronous communication technology (not real-time).  This category of software is used for recording demonstrations, remote technical assistance, sales presentations, and training.

